  "texts": [
    "We write D = C ⊔ I C ′ and say D is obtained by gluing C and C ′ along I.",
    "The subregions C and C ′ have associated surfaces Σ C and Σ C ′ whose outer boundary components both contain a boundary interval (see Section 3.3) I and I ′ respectively, determined by I as follows.",
    "Let m C,I be the set of marked boundary points of Σ C which lie on one of the edges of E I.",
    "Define m C ′,I similarly.",
    "Then we may define I as the smallest closed subinterval of ∂Σ C that contains B 1/3 (m) for each m ∈ m C,I, where B r (x) ⊂ R 2 is the closed ball or radius r centred on x ∈ R 2."
